{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ff9-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1519a"},"text":"§ 1519a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitation on procurement of binary chemical weapons","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ffa-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no funds may be obligated or expended after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-09-24"},"text":"September 24, 1983","children":[],"tail":", for the production of binary chemical weapons unless the President certifies to the Congress that for each 155-millimeter binary artillery shell or aircraft-delivered binary aerial bomb produced a serviceable unitary artillery shell from the existing arsenal shall be rendered permanently useless for military purposes."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ffb-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ffc-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Funds appropriated pursuant to the authorization of appropriations for the Army in section 101 of this Act may be used for the establishment of a production base for binary chemical munitions and for the procurement of components for 155-millimeter binary chemical artillery projectiles, but such funds may not be used for the actual production of binary chemical munitions before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1985","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ffd-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1), before the production of binary chemical munitions may begin after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1985","children":[],"tail":", the President must certify to Congress in writing that, in light of circumstances prevailing at the time the certification is made, the production of such munitions is essential to the national interest."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6ffe-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s1519a/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For purposes of this subsection, “production of binary chemical munitions” means the final assembly of weapon components and the filling or loading of components with binary chemicals.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idd10a6fff-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94/tXII/s1233"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–94, title XII, § 1233","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/695"},"text":"97 Stat. 695","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idd10a7000-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idd10a7001-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idd10a7002-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 101 of this Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(1), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/94/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Pub. L. 98–94","children":[],"tail":", title I, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/618"},"text":"97 Stat. 618","children":[],"tail":", which was not classified to the Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idd10a7003-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Department of Defense Authorization Act, 1984, and not as part of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/121/tIV/s409"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–121, title IV, § 409","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-11-19"},"text":"Nov. 19, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/209"},"text":"83 Stat. 209","children":[],"tail":", which comprises this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
